  <info>
    <title>Managing network using &cockpit;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="shalaka.harne@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>&cockpit; enables you create virtual networks and manage them.</para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <section><title>Creating a network</title>
  <procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
  <step><para>Click <guimenu>Create virtual network</guimenu>.</para></step>
<step><para> Enter a network name.</para></step>
<step><para>Select the <guimenu>Forward mode</guimenu> and the <guimenu>Device</guimenu> from their respective drop-down lists</para></step>
<step><para>Select the IP configuration, then provide the IPv4 and/or IPv6 address and prefix length.</para></step>
<step><para>To configure a DHCP range, select Set DHCP range and enter the Start and End values.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu>.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
<section><title>Activating a network</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page. and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Activate</guimenu> next to the desired network.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
<section><title>Deactivating a network</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page. and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Deactivate</guimenu> next to the desired network.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
<section><title>Deleting a network</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click the three-dot menu and select <guimenu>Delete</guimenu> next to the network you want to delete.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
</topic>
